canonical:
  title: 臘祭
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 蜡索萬物式陳苾苾之羞潛有多魚兼備莘莘之薦幸加聦享以答孝悰
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 臘祭
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 蜡索萬物。式陳苾苾之羞。潛有多魚。兼備莘莘之薦。幸加聦享。以答孝悰。
korean:
  title: 납제
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 사제(蜡祭 음력 1ㆍ2월에 만물에 크게 지내는 제사)에는 만물을 다하여[蜡索萬物] 향기로운 제수(祭羞)를 공손히 진설하고, 깊은 물의 섶에 많은 물고기가 있으므로, 푸짐한 제물을 겸비하였습니다. 다행히 총명하신 흠향을 주시어서 효도스러운 정성에 응답하옵소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1130_020_0060&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: The Winter Sacrifice
  author: Lee Gyubo
  language: eng
  text: The winter sacrifice gathers all things—we humbly arrange fragrant offerings with reverence. From deep waters teeming with fish, we have prepared abundant gifts. Grant us, spirits of keen discernment, your blessing that our filial hearts might be answered.
  footnotes:
    - The winter sacrifice (Laba Festival) was traditionally performed in the first and second lunar months as an offering to all things in nature and the spirits that govern them.
    - The imagery of abundant fish from deep waters symbolizes both material prosperity and the depth of natural abundance available for proper ritual observance.
